The measure, imposed by the European Union, aims to increase the protection of pedestrians, even if its mode of action, it can also help to prevent many collisions.
The assistant emergency braking is increasing the pressure on the brakes in the event of an emergency, the system detects by the kick given by the driver.
But it does not always maintained the pressure until the end.
According to a study conducted by the manufacturer of components for cars Bosch, a third of the drivers involved in an accident had not been able to rely on the brake before the collision, and half of them did not use the full force.
Up to 1,100 accidents
The intervention of the aid, revancha, requires the maximum the brake system, reducing the distance that the car needs to stop.
According to a study by the EU itself, if all cars were equipped with this type of elements, up to 1,100 fatal accidents in which pedestrians are involved could be avoided each year.
The reduction will be even more important with the so-called Intelligent Emergency Braking Systems: It is estimated that one of every four would be avoided.
In this case, the vehicle is equipped with a system that (through a radar or a camera) detects the obstacles and warns the driver, in addition to act slightly on the brakes.
